Day-2 Learnings
* Phising Attack
Phising attack is a type of cyber attack where the attacker pretends to be the trusted entity and tricks you into revealing your sensitive information or click on malicious links.
they usually steal your passwords, bank details, gain access to your accounts and access personal data.
Types of phising attacks: E-mail, SMS, voice, Social media, Spear phising attack( Targetted to one person where they have all of their personal data)

*HTTP(Hyper Text transfer protocol) VS HTTPS (Hyper Text transfer protocol Secure)
HTTP- standard protocol to transmit data in web. It operates over port 80. Data being transmitted is not encrypted.
Https- more secure version of HTTP. It operates over port 443. Data being transmitted is encrypted.
It uses SSL(secure socket layer) or TSL( transport layer security) to encrypt the data.

